nce%20with%20the%20Congress%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20seat%20sharing%20with%20them%2C%20move%20away%20from%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20and%20if%20not%20then%20Kejriwal%20will%20be%20arrested%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20the%20coming%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Atishi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20want%20to%20tell%20the%20BJP%20that%20you%20can%20send%20as%20many%20notices%2C%20as%20many%20summons%2C%20arrest%20all%20AAP%20leaders%2C%20hang%20us%20but%20we%20will%20not%20be%20scared%20of%20your%20threats.%20We%20have%20been%20fighting%20for%20democracy%20and%20the%20Constitution%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20do%20so.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20come%20as%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20AAP%20have%20reached%20the%20final%20stages%20of%20reaching%20seat%20sharing%20agreement%20across%20states%20including%20Delhi%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Goa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20final%20shape%20to%20seat%20sharing%20arrangements%20come%20only%20weeks%20after%20the%20AAP%20throwing%20the%20gauntlet%20earlier%20this%20month%20and%20offering%20only%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Faap-throws-down-gauntlet-to-congress-seat-sharing-delay%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20one%20seat%20to%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20capital%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20while%20saying%20it%20does%20not%20%E2%80%9Cdeserve%20a%20single%20seat%20on%20merit%E2%80%9D.%20While%20the%20national%20leadership%20of%20the%20Congress%20admitted%20to%20a%20delay%20in%20seat%20sharing%20talks%2C%20its%20Delhi%20unit%20said%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Cenergised%E2%80%9D%20to%20fight%20on%20all%20seven%20seats%20in%20the%20national%20capital.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETalks%20in%20final%20stage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPathak%20said%20today%20that%20the%20announcement%20on%20the%20alliance%20with%20the%20grand%20old%20party%20relating%20to%20all%20states%20will%20be%20done%20together%20and%20the%20talks%20are%20at%20%E2%80%9Cfinal%20stage%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20hopeful%20that%20the%20announcement%20will%20be%20done%20very%20soon%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPathak%20added%20that%20if%20Kejriwal%20is%20arrested%20there%20will%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctsunami%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country%20as%20people%20will%20take%20to%20the%20streets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20will%20be%20a%20tsunami%20in%20the%20country%20and%20all%20well%20meaning%20people%20will%20take%20to%20the%20roads%20and%20all%20their%20political%20calculations%20which%20they%20think%20will%20work%20if%20Kejriwal%20is%20arrested%20will%20be%20fall%20flat.%20I%20want%20to%20tell%20their%20political%20pundits%2C%20you%20are%20not%20dealing%20with%20any%20political%20party%20but%20are%20now%20trying%20to%20take%20on%20AAP.%20They%20are%20saying%20leave%20the%20alliance%20or%20we%20will%20arrest%20Kejriwal.%20We%20are%20not%20afraid%20of%20arrests%2C%20if%20we%20were%20then%20so%20many%20of%20our%20leaders%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20been%20in%20jail.%20We%20will%20not%20be%20scared.%20We%20are%20in%20the%20alliance%20not%20for%20our%20personal%20profit%20but%20for%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharadwaj%20said%20that%20the%20haste%20with%20which%20the%20BJP%20is%20trying%20to%20use%20central%20agencies%20to%20arrest%20Kejriwal%20shows%20its%20%E2%80%9Cnervousness%E2%80%9D%20ahead%20of%20the%20elections%20despite%20claims%20from%20top%20BJP%20leaders%20including%20prime%20minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20that%20the%20saffron%20party%20will%20cross%20400%20seats%20in%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBJP%E2%80%99s%20nervousness%20is%20showing.%20So%20they%20have%20decided%20to%20forget%20ED%2C%20and%20tell%20the%20CBI%20to%20quickly%20arrest%20Kejriwal%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bharadwaj.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20(BJP)%20think%20that%20if%20the%20Congress%20and%20AAP%20come%20together%2C%20then%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20difficulties%20will%20increase%20in%20those%20states%20where%20our%20alliance%20is%20there.%20They%20are%20making%20big%20statements%20of%20crossing%20400%20seats.%20The%20person%20who%20is%20promising%20to%20cross%20400%20seats%20won%E2%80%99t%20send%20CBI%20to%20an%20elderly%20former%20governor.%20These%20are%20not%20signs%20of%20%E2%80%98400%20%3Cem%3Epar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98.%20Ask%20any%20political%20scientist.%20One%20who%20is%20crossing%20400%20seats%20shows%20signs%20of%20love%2C%20not%20of%20fear%20and%20loss.%20We%20want%20to%20tell%20the%20centre%20and%20the%20BJP%20that%20you%20can%20arrest%20Kejriwal%20if%20you%20want%2C%20but%20Kejriwal%20and%20Congress%20alliance%20within%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20is%20ready%20to%20be%20formed%20and%20will%20not%20stop.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708681580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23151422%2FScreenshot-2024-02-23-at-3.13.48.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Farvind-kejriwal-bjp-congress-arrest%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20come%20as%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20AAP%20have%20reached%20the%20final%20stages%20of%20reaching%20seat%20sharing%20agreement%20in%20states%20including%20Delhi%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Goa%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20make%20an%20announcement%20soon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Farvind-kejriwal-bjp-congress-arrest%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Money%2C%20Power%2C%20Politics%20and%20Electoral%20Bonds%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20Preserves%20Sanctity%20of%20Electoral%20Process%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15213318%2FThe-unemployment-situation-2.gif%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20verdict%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20on%20the%20key%20questions%20related%20to%20transparency%20in%20financial%20contribution%20to%20political%20parties.%20Central%20to%20this%20verdict%20is%20not%20only%20an%20affirmation%20of%20the%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20but%20also%20the%20influence%20of%20money%20on%20the%20sanctity%20of%20electoral%20process%20and%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20in%20fostering%20participatory%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20deliberated%20on%20the%20challenge%20to%20a%20set%20of%20parliamentary%20laws%20which%20introduced%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20(%E2%80%9Cscheme%E2%80%9D)%20in%20January%202018%20and%20provided%20for%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20information%20pertaining%20to%20the%20financial%20contributions%20made%20to%20political%20parties%20and%20enabled%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties%20by%20removing%20cap%20on%20the%20funding%20by%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20primary%20issues%20were%20deliberated.%20First%2C%20whether%20the%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%20regarding%20contributions%20to%20political%20parties%20violated%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20of%20citizen%20as%20enshrined%20in%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Second%2C%20whether%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties%20infringed%20upon%20the%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20thereby%20violating%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERight%20to%20information%20of%20voter%20and%20participatory%20democracy%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20issue%2C%20the%20court%20examined%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20right%20to%20information%20extends%20to%20financial%20contribution%20made%20to%20political%20parties.%20While%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20court%20analysed%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20scope%20of%20Right%20to%20Information%20in%20two%20distinct%20phases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20phase%2C%20the%20scope%20was%20limited%20to%20open%20government%20and%20transparency.%20In%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20the%20court%20progressively%20expanded%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20and%20recognised%20the%20role%20of%20information%20in%20debate%2C%20discussion%2C%20and%20fostering%20democratic%20participation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20first%20and%20second%20phase%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20laid%20the%20foundational%20framework%20for%20the%20court%20to%20guarantee%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voter%20about%20the%20contesting%20candidates%20background%20including%20their%20criminal%20past%20in%20%3Cem%3EUnion%20of%20India%20v%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%202002%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EPUCL%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%202003%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20first%20issue%2C%20the%20court%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20political%20parties%20are%20relevant%20political%20units%20and%20are%20central%20to%20the%20democratic%20electoral%20process.%20Consequently%2C%20it%20affirmed%20that%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20extends%20to%20political%20parties%20given%20their%20significance%20in%20shaping%20the%20electoral%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opinion%20of%20the%20court%20was%20based%20on%20the%20assessment%20of%20the%20prominence%20accorded%20to%20the%20political%20parties%20in%20the%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20particularly%20under%20the%20tenth%20schedule%2C%20and%20their%20position%20within%20the%20legal%20framework%20related%20to%20the%20election%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20includes%20information%20about%20financial%20contribution%20to%20a%20political%20party.%20The%20court%20made%20a%20comprehensive%20analysis%20of%20the%20relationship%20between%20political%20inequality%20and%20economic%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20constitution%20mandates%20political%20equality%20by%20ensuring%20equal%20value%20and%20voice%20of%20each%20vote%20to%20influence%20government%20decisions%20and%20policy%2C%20economic%20inequality%20can%20still%20perpetuate%20political%20inequality.%20The%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20economic%20inequality%20allows%20the%20wealthy%20individuals%20and%20corporate%20to%20%E2%80%98get%20seat%20at%20the%20table%E2%80%99%20and%20influence%20not%20only%20the%20policy%20decisions%20but%20also%20the%20electoral%20outcome%20by%20virtue%20of%20their%20financial%20contributions%20to%20the%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20progressive%20reading%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20by%20the%20court%20to%20include%20financial%20contribution%20to%20political%20parties%20resulted%20from%20the%20recognition%20that%20such%20transparency%20enables%20voters%20to%20evaluate%20any%20potential%20quid%20pro%20quo%20between%20contributors%20and%20political%20parties.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20facilitates%20an%20assessment%20of%20the%20influence%20of%20money%20on%20policy%20decisions%20and%20electoral%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felectoral-bonds-narendra-modi-rbi%5C%22%3EModi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Tryst%20with%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Should%20Neither%20Be%20Forgotten%20Nor%20Forgiven%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnlimited%20funding%20and%20electoral%20corruption%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20addressed%20a%20crucial%20issue%20regarding%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties%2C%20which%20was%20made%20possible%20by%20amending%20Section%20182%20of%20the%20Companies%20Act%202013%2C%20that%20removed%20the%20cap%20on%20corporate%20donations%20to%20political%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20core%20of%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20lies%20the%20significant%20role%20of%20money%20in%20electoral%20politics%20as%20emphasised%20by%20the%20court%20throughout%20its%20judgment.%20Recognising%20the%20nexus%20between%20money%2C%20power%20and%20politics%2C%20the%20court%20highlighted%20its%20influence%20on%20electoral%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%2C%20in%20his%20concurring%20opinion%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20influence%20of%20money%20itself%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20and%20undermines%20the%20quality%20and%20integrity%20of%20governmental%20decision-making%20processes%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20question%20of%20unlimited%20funding%2C%20the%20court%20asserted%20the%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20within%20an%20electoral%20democracy%2C%20emphasising%20the%20sanctity%20and%20integrity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20as%20previously%20established%20in%20cases%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3EIndira%20Gandhi%20v.%20Raj%20Narain%201975%20and%20PUCL%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%202013%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20observed%20that%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20authorises%20companies%20to%20exert%20unrestrained%20influence%20over%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20fostering%20corruption%20in%20electoral%20financing.%20Thus%2C%20the%20court%20ruled%20that%20such%20practice%20violates%20the%20fundamental%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20is%20inherently%20arbitrary%20and%20violates%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERight%20to%20informational%20privacy%20of%20donors%20vs%20Right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20argument%20on%20informational%20privacy%20for%20donors%2C%20the%20court%20relied%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3EK.S.%20Puttaswamy%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%202017%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20held%20that%20the%20Constitution%20recognises%20the%20right%20to%20informational%20privacy%20of%20political%20affiliation%2C%20which%20also%20extends%20to%20the%20financial%20contributions%20made%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20noted%20that%20privacy%20regarding%20political%20affiliation%20is%20a%20prerequisite%20to%20exercising%20the%20freedom%20of%20political%20expression.%20The%20lack%20of%20privacy%20in%20political%20affiliation%20and%20the%20disclosure%20of%20information%20about%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20political%20beliefs%20could%20lead%20to%20disproportionate%20effects%2C%20such%20as%20voter%20surveillance%20and%20the%20suppression%20of%20dissenting%20opinions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20competing%20interests%20of%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voter%20and%20the%20informational%20privacy%20of%20donor%2C%20the%20court%20applied%20double%20proportionality%20standards%20%3Cem%3E(test%20applied%20by%20court%20to%20balance%20two%20conflicting%20fundamental%20right)%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20balance%20both%20the%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20observed%20that%20blanket%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%20as%20envisaged%20under%20the%20scheme%20heavily%20favoured%20informational%20privacy%20and%20did%20not%20adequately%20balance%20the%20competing%20interests.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20court%20held%20that%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20cannot%20be%20restricted%20based%20on%20the%20informational%20privacy%20of%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20defense%20that%20the%20scheme%20curbs%20the%20circulation%20of%20black%20money%20in%20electoral%20funding%20by%20incentivising%20donations%20through%20the%20banking%20channel%2C%20the%20court%20affirmed%20that%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20under%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20can%20be%20curtailed%20only%20on%20the%20limited%20grounds%20of%20restriction%20provided%20under%20Article%2019(2).%20The%20purpose%20of%20curbing%20black%20money%20cannot%20be%20traced%20to%20any%20of%20the%20grounds%2C%20and%20hence%20the%20court%20rejected%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20argument.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fillicit-bonds-scrapped-peoples-right-to-know-inseparable-from-free-and-fair-elections%5C%22%3E%20Illicit%20Bonds%20Scrapped%3A%20People%E2%80%99s%20Right%20to%20Know%20Inseparable%20From%20Free%20and%20Fair%20Elections%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20violation%20of%20privacy%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20strong%20assertion%20of%20the%20principle%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20election%2C%20and%20the%20role%20of%20right%20to%20information%20in%20nurturing%20participatory%20democracy%2C%20this%20verdict%20highlights%20two%20distinctive%20features.%20Firstly%2C%20it%20extends%20the%20right%20to%20information%20to%20political%20parties.%20This%20ruling%20would%20impact%20the%20issue%20originating%20from%20political%20parties%E2%80%99%20outright%20refusal%20to%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%202005.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20acknowledges%20the%20informational%20privacy%20of%20donors%2C%20including%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%2C%20however%2C%20opens%20the%20door%20for%20divergence%20in%20the%20scope%20of%20interpreting%20informational%20privacy%20to%20donors%20in%20view%20of%20the%20concurring%20opinion%20of%20Justice%20Khanna%20who%20slightly%20differed%20and%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20affairs%20of%20public%20company%20(or%20even%20a%20private%20company)%20are%20open%20to%20the%20shareholders%20and%20public%2C%20thus%20claim%20of%20the%20violation%20of%20privacy%20lacks%20substantial%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20reinstates%20faith%20in%20constitutional%20principles%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20through%20its%20interpretative%20exercise%20and%20provides%20clearer%20standards%20for%20the%20legislature%E2%80%99s%20adherence.%20It%20also%20reinforces%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20RTI%20as%20an%20important%20instrument%20for%20upholding%20our%20democratic%20values%20and%20expands%20on%20the%20understanding%20of%20the%20scope%20of%20informational%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYaqoob%20Alam%20is%20a%20lawyer%20at%20Saraf%20and%20Partners.%20He%20works%20on%20diverse%20issues%20related%20to%20technology%20law%20and%20public%20policy.%20Views%20expressed%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708681289000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmoney-power-politics-and-electoral-bonds-supreme-court-preserves-sanctity-of-electoral-process%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Given%20the%20competing%20interests%20of%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voter%20and%20the%20informational%20privacy%20of%20donor%2C%20the%20court%20applied%20double%20proportionality%20standards.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pakistan%20Supreme%20Court%20defends%20ruling%20on%20minorities%20after%20backlash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708680986000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107940865%2Cimgsize-20598.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpakistan-supreme-court-defends-ruling-on-minorities-after-backlash%2Farticleshow%2F107940868.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107940868.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPakistan's%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20come%20to%20the%20defense%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20Qazi%20Faez%20Isa%20after%20he%20faced%20bac