day%2C%20February%2022%2C%20%E2%80%9Caround%20noon%2C%20the%20ship%20was%20shown%20to%20be%20near%20Thilafushi%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20January%2023%2C%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20had%20stated%20that%20permission%20for%20docking%20had%20been%20granted%20to%20the%20ship%20after%20receiving%20a%20diplomatic%20request%20from%20the%20government%20of%20China%20for%20permission%20to%20make%20a%20port%20call%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20replenishment%20and%20rotation%20of%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Maldivian%20authorities%2C%20the%20ship%20will%20not%20be%20conducting%20any%20surveys%20in%20the%20Maldives%20waters%20even%20though%20it%20would%20be%20docked%20in%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20port.%20The%20statement%20said%20Maldives%20has%20always%20welcomed%20both%20civilian%20and%20military%20vessels%20from%20friendly%20nations%20to%20make%20port%20calls%20when%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fchinese-research-ship-moors-near-maldives-after-spending-a-month-in-indian-ocean%2Farticle67874951.ece%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CXiang%2520Yang%2520Hong%252003%2520began%2C.com%252C%2520a%2520news%2520portal.%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20February%2C%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Wang%20Wenbin%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CChina%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20research%20activities%20in%20relevant%20waters%20are%20for%20peaceful%20purposes%20and%20aimed%20at%20contributing%20to%20humanity%E2%80%99s%20scientific%20understanding%20of%20the%20ocean.%E2%80%9D%20On%20January%205%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20writes%20the%20newspaper%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhile%20denying%20entry%20to%20the%20Chinese%20ship%2C%20had%20said%20it%20had%20declared%20a%20moratorium%20on%20foreign%20research%20ships%20entering%20its%20waters%20for%20a%20year%20amid%20concerns%20from%20India%20over%20Chinese%20research%20vessels%20docking%20in%20its%20neighbourhood.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrilateral%20Coast%20Guard%20drill%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20writes%20that%20the%20Maldives%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20key%20maritime%20neighbour%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20Region%20(IOR)%20and%20occupies%20a%20special%20place%20in%20SAGAR%E2%80%99%20(Security%20and%20Growth%20for%20All%20in%20the%20Region)%20and%20the%20Neighbourhood%20First%20Policy%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20present%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2022%2C%20Coast%20Guards%20of%20Maldives%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20along%20with%20observers%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20joined%20in%20at%20the%20Trilateral%20Joint%20Exercise%20%E2%80%98DOSTI-16.%E2%80%99%20The%20Deccan%20Herald%20reports%20that%20even%20as%20Mal%C3%A9%20ignored%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20and%20allowed%20a%20%E2%80%98research%20vessel%E2%80%99%20of%20China%20to%20enter%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20territorial%20waters%20India%20has%20sent%20two%20ships%20of%20its%20coast%20guard%20to%20Maldives%20for%20the%20drill.%20The%20two%20ships%20of%20the%20Indian%20Coast%20Guard%20(ICG)%20are%2C%20ICGS%20Samarth%20and%20ICGS%20Abhinav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FIndiaCoastGuard%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40IndiaCoastGuard%3C%2Fa%3E%20Ship%20Samarth%20(with%20integral%20helo)%20and%20Abhinav%20entered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FMale%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23Male%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%20to%20participate%20in%20the%2016th%20edition%20of%20Exercise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FDOSTI%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23DOSTI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20trilateral%20exercise%20between%20the%20Coast%20Guards%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhash