2300269_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgm-s-cruise-prepares-to-resume-robotaxi-testing-after-suspension-124022300269_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgm-s-cruise-prepares-to-resume-robotaxi-testing-after-suspension-124022300269_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22About%20half%20of%20America's%20new%20college%20graduates%20are%20working%20in%20high%20school-level%20jobs%20like%20food%20service%20and%20retail%3A%20report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20university%20graduates%20celebrate.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d81dbcce7f1785b2e355b3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20group%20of%20university%20graduates%20celebrate.%3Cp%3Ekali9%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%20half%20of%20new%20college%20graduates%20in%20the%20US%20are%20working%20high%20school-level%20jobs%2C%20per%20new%20research.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAround%2052%25%20of%20recent%20graduates%20start%20their%20careers%20in%20jobs%20that%20don't%20need%20a%20degree%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMost%20of%20these%20underemployed%20graduates%20work%20in%20food%20services%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20office%20administration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%20of%20graduating%2C%20about%2052%25%20of%20people%20who%20recently%20earned%20bachelor's%20degrees%20in%20the%20US%20are%20working%20jobs%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20college%20education%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20joint%20report%20by%20two%20research%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20underemployed%20graduates%20%E2%80%94%2088%25%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20are%20working%20high%20school-level%20jobs%20such%20as%20office%20support%2C%20food%20service%2C%20and%20retail%20within%20five%20years%20of%20graduation%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstradaeducation.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FTalent-Disrupted.pdf%3Futm_source%3DStradaEducation.org%26utm_medium%3DWebsite%26utm_campaign%3DTalentDisrupted%26utm_content%3DDownloadButton%2520%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20data%20research%20firms%20Burning%20Glass%20Institute%20and%20the%20Strada%20Education%20Foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20published%20on%20Thursday%2C%20was%20based%20on%20a%20dataset%20of%20%3Cspan%3E60%20million%20people's%20careers%3C%2Fspan%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20including%20those%20of%2010.8%20million%20people%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20findings%20present%20a%20bleak%20outlook%20for%20new%20graduates%20hoping%20that%20a%20degree%20will%20guarantee%20them%20significantly%20better%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20college%20graduates%20typically%20earn%20more%20than%20those%20with%20only%20a%20high-school%20education%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20sizable%20share%20of%20graduates%20do%20not%20experience%20the%20economic%20outcome%20they%20expected%20from%20earning%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20in%20pay%20is%20significant.%20Underemployed%20graduates%20earn%20about%2025%25%20more%20than%20workers%20with%20only%20a%20high%20school%20diploma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20far%20less%20than%20they%20would%20make%20if%20they%20had%20found%20a%20job%20that%20requires%20a%20degree.%20People%20working%20college-level%20jobs%20earn%2088%25%20more%20than%20those%20with%20only%20a%20high%20school%20education%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20that%20the%20typical%20graduate%20working%20a%20college-level%20job%20earns%20around%2050%25%20more%20than%20an%20underemployed%20graduate%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMost%20underemployed%20graduates%20are%20in%20sales%20and%20office%20administration%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20graduates%20working%20high%20school-level%20jobs%20five%20years%20after%20finishing%20college%2C%20the%20most%20common%20occupations%20are%20clerk%20(1.09%20million%20graduates)%2C%20sales%20supervisor%20(1%20million)%2C%20retail%20sales%20worker%20(759%2C000)%2C%20salesperson%20(611%2C000)%2C%20and%20secretary%20(602%2C000).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20370%2C000%20of%20these%20graduates%20work%20in%20food%20and%20beverage%20services%2C%20while%20another%20350%2C000%20work%20in%20construction%2C%20per%20the%20report.%20At%20least%204.5%20million%20more%20graduates%20work%20other%20types%20of%20high%20school-level%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%20studied%20also%20matters%2C%20the%20researchers%20said.%20They%20found%20that%20fields%20requiring%20quantitative%20reasoning%2C%20such%20as%20engineering%20(26%25)%2C%20finance%20and%20accounting%20(29%25)%2C%20and%20computer%20science%20(36%25)%2C%20had%20the%20lowest%20five-year%20underemployment%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHealth-related%20work%2C%20including%20nursing%2C%20had%20the%20lowest%20underemployment%20rate%2C%20with%20only%2023%25%20of%20graduates%20not%20working%20college-level%20jobs%20five%20years%20after%20finishing%20their%20bachelor's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20public%20safety%20and%20security%20(68%25)%2C%20recreation%20and%20wellness%20studies%20(60%25)%2C%20and%20marketing%20and%20business%20management%20(57%25)%20had%20the%20highest%20five-year%20underemployment%20rates%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20get%20out%20of%20underemployment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20graduate%20starts%20their%20career%20underemployed%2C%20they're%20also%203.5%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20stay%20underemployed%2010%20years%20later%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20job%20following%20college%20graduation%20is%20critically%20important%20for%20most%20individuals%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2027%25%20of%20underemployed%20graduates%20eventually%20advance%20to%20college-level%20jobs%20in%20the%20next%2010%20years.%20But%20for%20every%20100%20graduates%2C%2045%20will%20still%20be%20underemployed%20a%20decade%20after%20earning%20their%20degrees%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20around%2021%25%20of%20graduates%20who%20start%20their%20careers%20in%20a%20college-level%20job%20eventually%20fall%20into%20underemployment%20by%20the%2010-year%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20an%20internship%20in%20your%20field%20of%20study%20vastly%20improves%20your%20chances%20of%20getting%20a%20college-level%20job%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20with%20internships%20before%20graduating%20had%20a%2048.5%25%20lower%20chance%20of%20being%20underemployed%20in%20their%20first%20year%20of%20working%2C%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20only%2029%25%20of%20college%20graduates%20secure%20a%20paid%20internship%20before%20they%20finish%20school%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20urging%20policymakers%20and%20universities%20to%20push%20students%20toward%20such%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaid%20internships%2C%20they%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Boffer%20a%20proven%20route%20to%20college-level%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20encouraged%20schools%20to%20provide%20personalized%20career%20coaching%2C%20which%20they%20said%20is%20increasingly%20showing%20itself%20to%20be%20useful%20for%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStudents%20deserve%20to%20understand%20what%20steps%20they%20can%20take%20to%20reduce%20underemployment%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20current%20ratio%20of%20students%20to%20career%20services%20staff%20at%20US%20colleges%20is%201%20to%202%2C263%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-new-us-graduates-work-high-school-level-jobs-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708668037000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d81df690413ab8e1d64777%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-new-us-graduates-work-high-school-level-jobs-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Around%2052%25%20of%20recent%20graduates%20in%20the%20US%20start%20their%20careers%20in%20jobs%20that%20don't%20need%20a%20college%20degree%2C%20per%20a%20new%20joint%20report%20by%20two%20research%20firms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhalf-new-us-graduates-work-high-school-level-jobs-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Healthcare%20firm%20Abridge%20secures%20%24150%20mn%20to%20develop%20AI%20model%20for%20clinicians%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708667915000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-09%2F22%2Ffull%2F1632331188-3896.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhealthcare-firm-abridge-secures-150-mn-to-develop-ai-model-for-clinicians-124022300261_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shiv%20Rao%2C%20CEO%20of%20Abridge%20and%20also%20a%20practicing%20cardiologist%2C%20said%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20use%20the%20fresh%20funding%20for%20hiring%20as%20well%20as%20acquiring%20and%20training%20purpose-built%20medical%20AI%20models%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhealthcare-firm-abridge-secures-150-mn-to-develop-ai-model-for-clinicians-124022300261_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhealthcare-fi