nters%20of%20America%20Inc.%2C%20the%20SEC%20said%20on%20Thursday.%20He%20liquidated%20his%20brokerage%20and%20retirement%20accounts%20and%20in%20February%202023%2C%20when%20BP%20announced%20it%20was%20buying%20TravelCenters%20of%20America%20at%20a%2074%25%20premium%2C%20Loudon%20made%20a%20%241.76%20million%20profit.%20His%20wife%2C%20then%20a%20BP%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%20manager%20who%20was%20working%20on%20the%20deal%2C%20was%20unaware%20of%20his%20trading%2C%20the%20regulator%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20lawsuits%20from%20the%20SEC%20and%20US%20prosecutors%20in%20Texas%2C%20Tyler%20got%20the%20idea%20to%20buy%20TravelCenters%20after%20learning%20of%20the%20potential%20deal%20from%20his%20wife%2C%20who%20was%20working%20on%20the%20deal%20in%20a%20home%20office%2020%20feet%20away.%20When%20he%20ultimately%20confessed%20to%20her%2C%20she%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20house%20and%20later%20filed%20for%20divorce.%20She%20reported%20his%20trades%20to%20BP%2C%20who%20then%20fired%20her%20despite%20finding%20no%20evidence%20that%20she%20knowingly%20leaked%20the%20deal%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SEC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20his%20settlement%2C%20Loudon%20agreed%20to%20give%20up%20the%20money%20he%20made%20on%20the%20transactions%20and%20pay%20a%20fine.%20Loudon's%20lawyer%2C%20Peter%20Zeidenberg%2C%20didn't%20immediately%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20BP%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20to%20buy%20TravelCenters%20of%20America%20Inc.%20for%20about%20%241.3%20billion%20gave%20the%20British%20oil%20major%20access%20to%20a%20network%20of%20US%20gas%20stations.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20the%20transaction%2C%20TravelCenters%20had%20a%20network%20of%20281%20locations%20in%2044%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20work-from-home%20era%20began%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20SEC%20has%20brought%20multiple%20insider-trading%20cases%20involving%20information%20overhear