80%94a%20de%20facto%20dictatorship%20in%20which%20all%20the%20power%20rests%20in%20Putin's%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20maintain%20a%20cult%20of%20personality%2C%20you%20have%20to%20use%20a%20lot%20of%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Matthew%20Schmidt%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20national%20security%20and%20political%20science%20at%20The%20University%20of%20New%20Haven%20who%20previously%20taught%20planning%20at%20the%20US%20Army's%20School%20of%20Advanced%20Military%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20a%20fundamentally%20weak%20style%20of%20government%20even%20if%20the%20person%20in%20power%20is%20a%20strongman%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPutin%20is%20committed%20to%20maintaining%20an%20illusion%20of%20total%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pilot's%20death%20was%20likely%20a%20case%20of%20Russia%20protecting%20its%20military%20morale%20by%20taking%20out%20a%20confirmed%20defector%20and%20scaring%20other%20would-be%20treasonists%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20message%20is%20loud%20and%20clear%3A%20We%20will%20find%20you%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world.%20We%20will%20kill%20you%20just%20to%20send%20a%20message%20to%20the%20next%20person%20thinking%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Schmidt%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20an%20extraordinary%20power%2C%20and%20Putin%20did%20it%20effectively%2C%20making%20sure%20it%20wound%20up%20in%20the%20news.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20display%20of%20power%20by%20the%20Russian%20state%2C%20while%20jarring%2C%20is%20not%20out%20of%20the%20norm%20for%20Putin's%20regime%2C%20which%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-of-people-putin-is-suspected-of-assassinating-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20of%20assassinations%20abroad%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Navalny's%20and%20the%20pilot's%20deaths%20fit%20Putin's%20playbook%20to%20a%20T%2C%20exemplifying%20the%20lengths%20to%20which%20the%20Russian%20regime%20will%20go%20to%20maintain%20the%20illusion%20of%20total%20power%2C%20Schmidt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20absolutely%20is%20a%20crackdown%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20recent%20deaths.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20a%20crackdown%20that%20is%20always%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20death%20of%20Navalny%2C%20who%20frequently%20challenged%20and%20openly%20criticized%20Putin%2C%20also%20represented%20a%20major%20win%20for%20the%20Russian%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Navalny%20represented%20the%20most%20formidable%20threat%20to%20Putin's%20regime%2C%20criticizing%20corruption%20in%20the%20Russian%20state%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-alexei-navalny-had-a-message-for-russians-if-he-died-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganizing%20powerful%20anti-Kremlin%20protests%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20specifics%20surrounding%20Navalny's%20death%20remain%20unclear.%20Russia's%20Federal%20Prison%20Service%20said%20Navalny%20died%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falexey-navalny-death-prison-looked-happy-healthy-video-court-putin-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elosing%20consciousness%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20a%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20how%20he%20wound%20up%20dead%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20was%20ultimately%20responsible%20for%20Navalny's%20demise%2C%20Simon%20Miles%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20Duke%20University's%20Sanford%20School%20of%20Public%20Policy%20and%20a%20historian%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20US-Soviet%20relations%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20were%20not%20for%20the%20regime%2C%20he%20would%20be%20alive%2C%26quot%3B%20Miles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENavalny's%20death%20shows%20Putin%20is%20easily%20threatened%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20experts%20said%20Navalny's%20death%2C%20rather%20than%20simply%20displaying%20Putin's%20power%2C%20actually%20highlighted%20his%20weakness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20guy%20locked%20up%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-russian-arctic-prison-where-alexey-navalny-spent-last-days-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520Friday%252C%2520Russia%2527s%2520Federal%2520Penitentiary%2Cmatter%2520what%2520the%2520weather%2520is.%2522%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egulag%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20too%20high%20a%20threat%20to%20live%2C%20that%20tells%20me%20Putin%20thinks%20his%20position%20is%20extremely%20vulnerable%2C%26quot%3B%20Miles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20total%20control%20over%20this%20person's%20life%2C%20and%20you%20choose%20to%20extinguish%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20coercive%20power%2C%20not%20an%20impressive%20form%20of%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20death%20was%20undoubtedly%20meant%20to%20send%20a%20message%20to%20other%20would-be%20opposition%20leaders%2C%20experts%20said%2C%20especially%20as%20Putin%20prepares%20for%20a%20presidential%20election%20in%20less%20than%20a%20month%20that%20he%20is%20all%20but%20certain%20to%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20can%20arrest%20and%20kill%20at%20will.%20Being%20able%20to%20visit%20terror%20upon%20anyone%20you%20want%20is%20a%20kind%20of%20strength%2C%26quot%3B%20Schmidt%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20a%20strength%20that%20will%20eventually%20turn%20on%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20began%20in%20February%202022%2C%20Russia%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-purges-advisors-but-hes-responsible-for-misinformation-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPutin%20was%20responsible%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20creating%20an%20autocratic%20culture%20of%20fear%20that%20could%20eventually%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20collapse%20is%20likely%20still%20years%20down%20the%20line%2C%20Schmid