file%20cases%20in%20celebrities%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbruce-willis-diagnosis-frontotemporal-dementia-symptoms-treatment-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBruce%20Willis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20whose%20family%20announced%20his%20diagnosis%20in%20February%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20currently%20no%20cure%20or%20treatment%20for%20the%20condition%2C%20and%20it%20is%20known%20to%20progress%20over%20time%2C%20causing%20further%20decline%20in%20patients'%20ability%20to%20make%20decisions%20and%20communicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20of%20frontotemporal%20dementia%3A%20difficulty%20communicating%2C%20changes%20to%20mood%20and%20behavior%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFrontotemporal%20dementia%20refers%20to%20a%20group%20of%20disorders%20caused%20by%20nerve%20cell%20damage%20to%20areas%20of%20the%20brain%20behind%20the%20forehead%20(in%20the%20frontal%20lobe)%20and%20behind%20the%20ears%20(in%20the%20temporal%20lobes).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20parts%20of%20the%20brain%20help%20control%20language%20and%20behavior%2C%20so%20people%20with%20the%20condition%20can%20experience%20symptoms%20such%20as%20difficulty%20communicating%2C%20impulsive%20actions%2C%20or%20major%20personality%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinic.org%2Fdiseases-conditions%2Fprimary-progressive-aphasia%2Fsymptoms-causes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrimary%20progressive%20aphasia%20falls%20under%20the%20umbrella%20of%20FTD.%3C%2Fa%3E%20It%20is%20a%20condition%20that%20affects%20a%20person's%20ability%20to%20communicate.%20Symptoms%20begin%20slowly%20and%20gradually%2C%20but%20over%20time%20can%20cause%20people%20to%20lose%20the%20ability%20to%20speak%2C%20write%2C%20or%20understand%20language%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrontotemporal%20dementia%20can%20also%20have%20symptoms%20such%20as%20memory%20loss%2C%20but%20unlike%20other%20forms%20of%20dementia%20